					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex; Yemenite semi-cursive script of 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper codex. </support>
								<extent>151 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>270</height>
										<width>205</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>258</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>151 folios (+2 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each. Modern restoration (leaves stuck on paper). </p>
									<p>Signatures in Hebrew letters and catchwords at the beginning of a quire. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Some folios damaged, restored on paper. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="38" writtenLines="38">
									<p>Has some marginal notes and additions. </p>
									<p>Mem and shin are truncated in the lines. </p>
									<p>Beginnings of new chapters are written in larger characters. </p>
									<p>Folio 15v should be read after 16r. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="3">
							<summary>Yemenite semi-cursive script of 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus n="1v"/>due to a recent hand.</p>
								<p>
									<locus from="148r" to="151v"/>due to a Yemenite contemporary hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>On folio 79r are four short midrashic passages on Deuteronomy.</p>
							<p>A note of sale, dated <date calendar="Seleucid">2028 </date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1717</date>), between <name type="person" role="owner">Ya῾akov ben Se῾id ibn Daud</name>  and <name type="person" role="owner">Yehosaf ben Se῾adia ben Avraham ben Mosheh</name>: folio 1r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Shekhar ibn Al-Sari</name>: inscribed 1r, 78v. </p>
						</additions>
